{
  "local_port": 46892,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the use of a meta tag in HTML?",
  "response": "Meta tags in HTML are used to provide metadata about a webpage, which is information about the webpage that isn't displayed directly on the page itself. They are placed within the `<head>` section of an HTML document and serve various purposes. Here are some common uses for meta tags:\n\n1. **Character Set Declaration**: Indicates the character encoding for the document, which is crucial for properly displaying text.\n   ```html\n   <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n   ```\n\n2. **Viewport Settings**: Controls the layout on mobile browsers, specifying how the page should be displayed on different devices.\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n   ```\n\n3. **Keywords**: Provides search engines with keywords relevant to the page's content, though it's less relevant today due to changes in how search engines rank pages.\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"HTML, CSS, JavaScript\">\n   ```\n\n4. **Description**: Offers a brief summary of the page, which search engines often use in search results to describe the page.\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"description\" content=\"This is a sample webpage that demonstrates meta tags in HTML.\">\n   ```\n\n5. **Author**: Helps to specify the author of the document.\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"author\" content=\"John Doe\">\n   ```\n\n6. **Robots**: Instructs web crawlers (like those from search engines) on how to index the content of the page.\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow\">\n   ```\n\n7. **Refresh**: Refreshes the page after a specified number of seconds or redirects the user to a different URL.\n   ```html\n   <meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"30\">\n   ```\n\n8. **Social Media Tags**: Tags for platforms like Facebook (Open Graph) and Twitter to enhance how links appear when shared.\n   ```html\n   <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Sample Webpage Title\">\n   ```\n\nMeta tags play a crucial role in search engine optimization (SEO), user experience, and ensuring proper rendering of webpages across different devices and platforms.",
